   <head>Epigrammi - XIV. De Caesare Borgia.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1">
     <l n="1">Qui modo prostratos jactarat cornibus ursos,</l>
     <l n="2">In latebras taurus concitus ecce fugit.</l>
     <l n="3">Nec latebras putat esse satis sibi: Tybride toto</l>
     <l n="4">Cingitur, et notis vix bene fidit aquis.</l>
     <l n="5">Terruerat montes mugitibus: obvia nunc est,</l>
     <l n="6">Et facilis cuivis praeda sine arte capi.</l>
     <l n="7">Sed tamen id magnum, nuper potuisse vel ursos</l>
     <l n="8">Sternere, nunc omnes posse timere feras.</l>
     <l n="9">Ne tibi, Roma, novae desint spectacula pompae;</l>
     <l n="10">Amphitheatrales reddit arena jocos.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
